owl:Ontology.dc:creator: Megan Katsumi
owl:Ontology.dc:description: This ontology provides a generic representation of resources that contain core properties generic across all transportation uses. We take the view presented in the TOVE model (Fadel, Fox, and Gruninger, 1994) that "...being a resource is not an innate property of an object but a property that is derived from the role the object plays with respect to an activity". The definition of a resource is dependent on its participation in an activity occurrence, so the Resource ontology is in fact an extension of the Activity ontology. In this sense, Resources are a class of manifestations, so that rather than have a specialized Resource-perdurant (PD) class, a Resource is a manifestation of some other perdurant class in the ontology. For example, an instance of a Vehicle that is a manifestation of some VehiclePD may also be an instance of a resource, whereas some other instance of a Vehicle that is some later manifestation of the same VehiclePD may not be a Resource, or it may be a different Resource.
owl:Ontology.dc:title: iCity Resource Ontology
owl:Ontology.rdfs:comment:
Developed as part of the overall iCity ontology effort, the iCity-Resource ontology is designed to capture concepts related to resources. Changes from previous version: -modifications required for update to iCity-Activity ontology -removed ResourceType class (much like activities, types of resources shall be captured via various classes of resources) -Resource consumedBy or usedBy only Activity -Resource participatesIn min 1 Activity -Resource usedBy only Activity -NonDivisibleResource usedBy exactly 1 Activity -removed consumedInOccurrence, usedInOccurrence -old axioms relating Resources to ActivityOccurrences removed
Copyright @ 2016 Megan Katsumi, iCity Research Group

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The WGS84 altitude of a SpatialThing (decimal meters above the local reference ellipsoid).
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: altitude

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The WGS84 latitude of a SpatialThing (decimal degrees).
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: latitude

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The relation between something and the point, or other geometrical thing in space, where it is. For example, the realtionship between a radio tower and a Point with a given lat and long. Or a relationship between a park and its outline as a closed arc of points, or a road and its location as a arc (a sequence of points). Clearly in practice there will be limit to the accuracy of any such statement, but one would expect an accuracy appropriate for the size of the object and uses such as mapping .
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: location

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The WGS84 longitude of a SpatialThing (decimal degrees).
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: longitude

owl:ObjectProperty.dc:description: Added for organizational purposes, to identify all properties defined in the Resource ontology.

owl:Class.dc:description: A Resource is a generic representation of some Thing that can be "used" in an Activity. A Resource may have some Location, amount or availability, according to the definition of the Manifestation or TimeVaryingEntity. A Resource must be classified as some Resource Type. A Resource may participate in some Activity Occurrence. A specific Resource may be used in or consumed in some activity occurrence.
Added for organizational purposes, to identify all classes defined in the Resource ontology.
